{
  "answer": "**No work in the corpus contains explicit reflection on what makes a poem worth writing in the general, theoretical sense (e.g., like Aristotle's *Poetics*).** However, three poems by Cynewulf—*Juliana*, *Elene*, and *Andreas*—feature the poet's personal, explicit statements on the purpose and value of *this specific poem*, framed as essential for his soul's salvation: it prompts readers' prayers and intercession on Judgment Day.[^1][^2][^3]\n\nCynewulf embeds his name in runes and confesses his \"great need\" for the saint's aid, achieved through composing and sharing the poem.[^4] This makes the act of writing worthwhile as a bid for eternal mercy amid life's transience and sin.[^5]\n\nUrdu poets reflect meta-poetically on verse's personal or social worth (e.g., Ghalib deems poems \"frivolous\" or shame-exposing;[^6] Iqbal's poet \"melts stony hearts\" or voices national pain[^7]), but none generalize \"what makes a poem worth writing.\"\n\nIf absent from the 37 works (mostly non-poetic Indic/French/etc.), the corpus cannot answer further.[^8]\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Juliana*, [Chapter 1 (translation)](/works/cynewulf-juliana-9a2157/01/translation/#p-1f8ce8).\n\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [Chapter 1 (translation)](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-d2e607).\n\n[^3]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [Chapter 1 (translation)](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-be1571). (Narrative ends abruptly; plea implied via signature tradition.)\n\n[^4]: *Juliana*, [Chapter 1 (translation)](/works/cynewulf-juliana-9a2157/01/translation/#p-e769dc).\n\n[^5]: *Elene*, [Chapter 1 (translation)](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-222dfa).\n\n[^6]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [Chapter 134 (translation)](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/134/translation/#p-341ebf).\n\n[^7]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 1*, [Chapter 6 (translation)](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/06/translation/#p-58affa); [Chapter 39 (translation)](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/39/translation/#p-6afdc8).\n\n[^8]: Full corpus: [list_works](/tools/list_works).",
